Today marks the first ever National Black Voter Day. It‚Äôs an opportunity to recognize the power of the Black vote and to celebrate the numerous and invaluable contributions of the Black community to our nation and democracy. Black Americans ‚Äî specifically Black women ‚Äî are the backbone of the Democratic Party. Their ideas, their energy, their support, and their organizing power are vital to our victory in November.

Democrats know our democracy works best when everyone participates. Not only do Black voters have the power to decide this consequential election, they will be indispensable in guaranteeing Democratic victories up and down the ballot. That‚Äôs why the GOP has launched a full-fledged voter suppression campaign to try and suppress the Black vote. Make no mistake: The GOP has shown time and again that they‚Äôre willing to silence the Black community to protect their reelection chances. 

As a party, we are committed to listening to Black Americans as they make their voices heard. And we‚Äôll continue to fight alongside the Black community, litigating in the courts to end discrimination at the ballot box and providing the resources they need to cast their ballot. And as part of that commitment, we've recently relaunched IWillVote.com to be a one-stop shop for voters to get accurate and up-to-date voting information. Make your voting plan and #ReclaimYourVote.
